Former SAA Interim CEO and current Mango CEO, Nico Bezuidenhout is finalizing his court testimony into whether former SAA Chairperson Dudu Myeni should be declared a delinquent director. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Former SAA interim CEO Nico Bezuidenhout returned to the stand on Tuesday to testify on the conduct of former board chairperson Dudu Myeni. WATCH: Testimony about SAA operations continues According to Bezuidenhout, Myeni halted a deal between the airline and Emirates worth approximately a billion rand. He says Myeni never involved or provided any feedback to SAA executives after she had meetings with the transport minister about the deal. Former SAA interim CEO, Nico Bezuidenhout returns to the stand on Tuesday to testify on the conduct of former board chairperson Dudu Myeni.